<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four options end the same way: a completed AI Documentation Template. The path you pick changes what AI you use and what question you ask.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can use an AI on a low-stakes question and produce a complete, specific AI Documentation Template — including at least one specific thing the AI got wrong.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Gemini on "How do tides work?"</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Use Gemini (free through AISC Workspace) on the question. Save the conversation. OPVL the response. Fill out the full template.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Compare two AIs on the same question</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask "How do tides work?" to both Gemini and Claude. OPVL each response separately. Document both. Where do they disagree, and why?</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Push back with The Skeptic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Ask the same question of The Skeptic AI partner. Notice what it questions in your prompt and in the answer. Document the back-and-forth.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Practice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pick your own low-stakes topic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Not tides — something else genuinely low-stakes (how do rainbows form? why is the sky blue?). Use any AI. Full template. Bring your "one thing it got wrong" to the table share.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

